{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":273141,"duration_api_ms":261885,"num_turns":34,"result":"","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"51431a23-12a6-48a1-890f-80c6c891ed52","total_cost_usd":1.4467704999999995,"usage":{"input_tokens":29,"cache_creation_input_tokens":72648,"cache_read_input_tokens":1445451,"output_tokens":10794,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":72648,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":29,"outputTokens":10794,"cacheReadInputTokens":1445451,"cacheCreationInputTokens":72648,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":1.4467704999999995,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000}},"permission_denials":[],"structured_output":{"amendments":[{"body":"Extract the duplicated journal details rendering logic into a single shared function. `CompletionJournalDetails::render()` in `src/adapters/fs.rs:2347` and `completion_event_details()` in `src/contexts/milestone_record/service.rs:239` produce the same comma-delimited format independently. If either is modified without the other, the journal repair path (`repairable_completion_event`) will silently fail to merge entries — falling through to append duplicates instead of backfilling. Consolidate into one function (e.g., on `TaskRunEntry` or a shared helper) called by both sites.","rationale":"These two functions must stay in lockstep for journal repair to work. They are in different files with no compile-time or test-time coupling — a change to one will not produce any error or test failure, only silent duplicate journal entries that accumulate over time. This is the highest-severity maintainability risk in the changeset."},{"body":"Guard against field values containing the `, ` delimiter in `CompletionJournalDetails::parse()` (src/adapters/fs.rs:2280). The `outcome_detail` field is free-form text and can plausibly contain commas followed by spaces. While the current `split_once(\", detail=\")` approach handles a trailing detail value correctly, the intermediate `split_required` calls for `project=`, `run=`, and `plan_hash=` would misparse if any of those values contained `, `. Add a brief code comment or debug_assert documenting the assumption that project_id/run_id/plan_hash are simple identifiers that never contain `, `.","rationale":"The parsing works correctly today because IDs are well-behaved. But the assumption is implicit and a future caller could pass a project_id containing a comma. A comment or assertion makes this contract explicit and prevents a subtle data-corruption scenario where repaired journal entries silently drift from lineage entries."}],"summary":"The changes are correct and well-tested. The Paused status fix in `reconcile_snapshot_from_lineage` properly prevents Paused milestones from being reset to Ready during completion reconciliation. The journal repair logic in `append_event_if_missing` correctly identifies backfillable completion events and merges them without creating duplicates. The `LockAttemptSnapshotStore` tightening is a good defensive test-helper improvement. All 667 tests pass and clippy is clean. Two maintainability concerns: (1) duplicated format-rendering logic between `fs.rs` and `service.rs` that must stay in sync for repair to work, and (2) implicit assumption in the ad-hoc parser that ID fields never contain `, `."},"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"2710b1e8-12e4-4cc2-a587-4ded10cb4fc6"}
